<TEXT>
a drifter who supported himself 
and his flair for new wave clothing by gambling goes on trial 
monday on charges he sexually assaulting two aspiring teenage 
models and murdered their chaperones 
herbert james coddington 29 is accused of luring reno nev 
modeling school owner maybelle mabs martin 69 her friend 
dorothy dottie walsh 67 and the teenagers to his south lake 
tahoe mobile home last may with the ruse of making an antidrug 
videotape 
the women were strangled and their bodies stuffed in green 
plastic trash bags the girls then aged 12 and 14 were imprisoned 
in a sounddeadened room in the trailer where they remained for two 
days until fbi agents stormed in freed the girls and recovered the 
victims bodies 
defense lawyers have indicated coddington who faces death in 
the gas chamber if convicted will plead insanity 
we dont say he didnt do it said attorney steve tapson 
jury selection will begin monday in superior court in 
placerville calif where the case was moved because of extensive 
news coverage following his arrest here on may 18 1987 
last july coddington was charged with another murder he was 
accused of killing sheila keister 12 whose battered body was 
found in the desert in august 1981 just outside las vegas nev 
where she was abducted while playing 
in high school coddington was known as herb a quiet loner 
who didnt date and was said to be a math whiz possibly explaining 
his gambling abilities 
prosecutor ron tepper said the defendants successes at the 
poker blackjack and baccarat tables show were not dealing with 
somebody who is intellectually impoverished were dealing with 
somebody who has some gift 
although he had been unemployed for some time before his arrest 
coddington drove a new bmw on loan from a south lake tahoe car 
dealership which became the key link that led to his arrest and 
the rescue of the girls 
coddington had made the rounds of renoarea modeling agencies in 
the week before the girls and their chaperones disappeared looking 
for blonde allamerican girls for the purported videotaping 
session 
while most of the agency representatives remembered only a 
dirtylooking man with grimy hair who smelled bad one recalled the 
bmw and its dealers license plate 
neither side in the case has discussed any motive and tapson 
said his client is violently antidrug and opposed to drinking 
smoking and coffee 
