<TEXT>
the rt rev frederick houk borsch was 
ordained as the fifth bishop of the episcopal diocese of los 
angeles in ceremonies that combined ancient rites with modern 
ethnic concerns 
about 3000 members of southern californias diverse 
episcopalian community attended saturdays ordination at the sports 
arena including more than 20 episcopalian bishops from around the 
world and clergy from other faiths 
in a ritual dating to the christian churchs earliest days 
borsch 52 knelt before the denominations leader presiding 
bishop edmond lee browning as visiting bishops laid hands on him 
and prayed said dan crossland a video consultant with the diocese 
the ethnic and cultural differences of the dioceses 151 
congregations were emphasized by the presence of a mariachi band 
along with a traditional choir 
borsch was presented with the bishops robes and staff of 
office and received his miter from janice rusack the widow of his 
predecessor robert c rusack who died in july 1986 crossland 
said 
he received symbolic presentations including bread water and 
oil 
borsch who was elected bishop at a diocesan convention on jan 
8 will head a diocese comprised of 80000 people scattered 
throughout los angeles ventura santa barbara orange and san 
bernardino counties and half of riverside county 
borsch was dean of the chapel at princeton university a post he 
held since 1981 before that he was dean of the church divinity 
school of the pacific in berkeley calif and taught at various 
seminaries and colleges 
he is married and the father of three grown sons 
</TEXT>
