five palestinians went on trial sunday on 
charges they killed five britons and two sudanese in terrorist 
attacks last month at a hotel and a club frequented by foreigners 
the defendants who face the death penalty if convicted refused 
defense lawyers and claimed judge ahmed bashir already made up his 
mind they were guilty 
they told the court they were strugglers for the sake of the 
palestinian cause 
judge bashir calmly replied his verdict will be based only on 
evidence before the court he consented to a prosecution request 
for the court to appoint a lawyer and adjourned the closeddoor 
trial until next sunday 
the palestinians are charged with premeditated murder 
participation in murder and possession of illegal arms in 
connection with bombing and shooting incidents may 15 
the attacks occurred at the acropol hotel which caters mostly 
to foreigners and the sudan club which is reserved for british 
and commonwealth nationals 
the seven victims included a fourmember british family 
twentyone others mostly foreigners were also wounded in the 
attacks 
the defendants arrested shortly after the attacks had lebanese 
passports and claimed to be affiliated with the terrorist abu nidal 
group abu nidal whose real name is sabry banna heads a faction 
of the palestine liberation organization that opposes plo leader 
yasser arafat 
security sources said the defendants told questioners they were 
sent to avenge the assassination of khalil wazir or abu jihad the 
secondranking man in the plo who was killed april 16 in tunis 
allegedly by an israeli team 
the defendants are mustafa gasim rufai 26 imad ahmed huwilo 
23 hassan gasim 25 sharif izzat atawi 22 and ibrahim fusaei 30 
