an old city jail with medievalstyle turrets and 
thick stone walls would be transformed into a complex of 67 
lowcost apartments for working poor people under an ambitious 
project by an urban ministry 
the atlanta stockade once a debtors prison is listed in the 
national register of historic places from 1897 until the 1920s it 
housed criminals except for limited use by the citys school 
board the building has been empty for most of the past 60 years 
